The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Ill after chocolate
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Ill after chocolate
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Two children were taken ill after eating a bar of chocolate of a prominent brand on Wednesday evening. Trisha Dey, 5, and Seema Singh, 15, neighbours on Bhowanipores Mohini Mohan Road, had bought the chocolate from a local shop. Trisha has recovered after taking medicines but Seema had to be admitted to hospital. The fathers of both girls lodged police complaints, following which the shop-owner and his brother were arrested.        
	Plea: Home secretary Samar Ghosh said on Thursday that the state would approach court for the release of 220 mentally challenged persons lodged in various jails.        
	FIR: The fire department on Friday lodged an FIR against Abhishek Goyal, the owner of the plastic goods factory in Salkia that was gutted in a fire on Wednesday morning.        
	Detained: Five men were detained on Thursday for allegedly trying to kidnap Mohan Sarkar, an Andaman-based trader. Piyush Mondal and four others dragged Sarkar into a taxi while he was standing on Circular Garden Reach Road around 5.30pm and demanded Rs 70,000. The driver became suspicious and brought the taxi to Hastings police station, where the five were detained.                                                                                                                                                          
